cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with image fusion using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of hyperspectral imaging, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed model-based approach and iterative algorithm involve optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of deep neural networks for learning the proximal operators and model parameters falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
